<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>What is the ROI of content marketing?</strong></p>
<p>Content marketing returns an average of $3 for every $1 spent, compared to $1.80 for paid advertising. Some industries see higher returns. SaaS content marketing averages 19:1 ROI. Email marketing delivers $36 to $42 per $1 spent. The ROI depends on consistency, quality, and measurement.</p>
<p><strong>How many businesses use content marketing?</strong></p>
<p>91% of B2B marketers use content marketing. 80% of businesses use blogs as a marketing tool. The adoption rate is near-universal among growth-focused companies.</p>
<p><strong>What percentage of marketers use AI for content?</strong></p>
<p>89% of marketers now use AI for content creation. 97% of content marketers plan to use AI in their workflows. The most common uses are ideation (74%), outlining (61%), and drafting (44%).</p>
<p><strong>Is blogging still effective in 2026?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Businesses that blog generate 55% more traffic and 67% more leads. 7.5 million blog posts are published daily, which means competition is high, but businesses that prioritize <a href="/blog/seo-content-writing/">SEO content writing</a> and publish consistently are 13x more likely to see positive ROI.</p>
<p><strong>How often should a business publish content?</strong></p>
<p>The data supports consistent publishing over sporadic bursts. Businesses publishing 6 to 8 SEO-optimized posts per month build effective topic clusters within 6 to 12 months. Quality and keyword targeting matter more than raw volume.</p>
<p>Every content marketing decision should start with data. Bookmark this page, cite the stats that support your strategy, and check back quarterly for updates.</p>
